{ Now  12.Be2  actually transposes tothis line earlier on, but the most critical move here is long castle. }
12. O-O-O { The most critical. } 12... Qc7
{ The move I played against Levon.  12...Rc8  also can be investigated,   but I had a particular idea here after  12...Qc7. }
13. c4
{ This is a very counterintuitive move, playing from the king, before even moving it across, but the idea is to be able to meet Nb6 with Qa5! and not lose the d5 pawn in the process. }
13... a5 14. Kb1
