{ A rare move, but a decent one. White just wants to get a playable position. }
6... e6
{ A typical idea in this line, to recapture on d6 in the most traditional fashion, with a bishop. }
7. Nxd4 Bxd6
{ We just want to finish our development with castle and Nc6. White's most popular setup is to fianchetto the bishop here, but also if he doesn't we just develop naturally. }
8. g3 Nc6
{ Starting with this move is slightly clever. Now if White takes  9.Nxc6  bxc6  and plays  10.Bg2  we have  10...Ba6!  stopping him from castling comfortably. }
